<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-19T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-19T15:00:00-05:00" n="747" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d747">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5240: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-19T21:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">September 19,
                                        1919, 9 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 11:40
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>4280. Referring telegrams from <persName corresp="#p_CF1">Cole</persName>, Archangel, repeated to the Department by Embassy,
                            London, under numbers 2903<note n="67" xml:id="d747fn67">Dated Aug. 27,
                                3 p.m., <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_657">p.
                                    657</ref>.</note> and 2972<note n="68" xml:id="d747fn68">Not
                                printed.</note> and to Department’s inquiry communicated by
                            Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_DJW1">Davis</persName>,<note n="69" xml:id="d747fn69">No. 5946, Sept. 10, 6 p.m., to the Ambassador in
                                Great Britain, <ref target="#pg_661">p. 661</ref>.</note> the
                            Council of Four is not contemplating any measures to study [<hi rend="italic">steady?</hi>] or support popular movement in Archangel
                            district. It is unlikely that this subject will be approached by the
                            Peace Conference as I believe this question should be handled by the
                            Foreign Offfice[s]. Believe it would be well to give publicity to the
                            nature and <pb facs="0775" n="663" xml:id="pg_663"/> accomplishment of
                            Zemstvo and Municipal Assembly in Archangel as set forth in <persName corresp="#p_CF1">Cole</persName>’s reports.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_PFL"><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></persName></signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Mission</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>